edu.utsa.fileflow.cfg

Class FileFlowListenerImpl

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.utsa.fileflow.antlr.FileFlowBaseListener
      • edu.utsa.fileflow.cfg.FileFlowListenerImpl
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    edu.utsa.fileflow.antlr.FileFlowListener, org.antlr.v4.runtime.tree.ParseTreeListener

    public class FileFlowListenerImpl
extends edu.utsa.fileflow.antlr.FileFlowBaseListener
    This class will be responsible for handling entry and exit points when traversing through ANTLR's parse tree. Methods within FileFlowBaseListener can be overridden to be used as hooks for when the ParseTreeWalker visits or leaves a node.
    Author:
    Rodney Rodriguez

      • updateLast

        private void updateLast(FlowPoint newLast)
        Updates class global last variable. If the last was of type If, Else-if or Else, then it will not point to the new last. This is because IfType flow points have their own way of connecting flow points.
        Parameters:
        newLast - The last flow point created.
